@mamija the problem in my case was that I put the `.ethereum` folder on a mounted volume which had only 100 IOPS provisioned. It turns out that `geth` requires _much_ more than that. 
The solution was to use faster type of storage during the first sync, than stop `geth` and move the folder to the target drive.
I doubt that you have the same problem  - if you're not a programmer I find it unlikely that you are fiddling with EBS volumes...
